The paper focuses on the application of deep convolutional neural networks for noise reduction in CT images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for optimization also suggests a potential fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of parallelized $1\times 1$ CNNs, called Network in Network, suggests a potential fit for the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on medical imaging suggests a potential fit for the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
